TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Goal Programming Approach to Urban-Suburban Location Preferences
AU  - Courtney, James F.
AU  - Klastorin, Theodore D.
AU  - Ruefli, Timothy W.
Y1  - 1972/02/01
PY  - 1972
DA  - 1972/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.18.6.B258
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.18.6.B258
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - B-258
EP  - B-268
VL  - 18
IS  - 6
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Recent efforts in the area of modelling activities in the urban environment have been concentrated on the use of simulation techniques. In this paper the problem of population location in a metropolitan area is treated in an analytic model employing a goal programming formulation. A target population is broken into groups which then compete for a share of limited capacity in a number of urban sectors. The possible usefulness of this approach to urban planning, real estate development, and transportation systems design is illustrated through the theoretical development and the presentation of a numerical model.
AB  - Recent efforts in the area of modelling activities in the urban environment have been concentrated on the use of simulation techniques. In this paper the problem of population location in a metropolitan area is treated in an analytic model employing a goal programming formulation. A target population is broken into groups which then compete for a share of limited capacity in a number of urban sectors. The possible usefulness of this approach to urban planning, real estate development, and transportation systems design is illustrated through the theoretical development and the presentation of a numerical model.
