TY  - JOUR
T1  - On the N-Job One-Machine, Sequence-Independent Scheduling Problem with Tardiness Penalties: A Branch-Bound Solution
AU  - Shwimer, Joel
Y1  - 1972/02/01
PY  - 1972
DA  - 1972/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.18.6.B301
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.18.6.B301
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - B-301
EP  - B-313
VL  - 18
IS  - 6
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - An efficient branch-bound algorithm is presented for solving the n-job, sequence-independent, single machine scheduling problem where the goal is to minimize the total penalty costs resulting from tardiness of jobs. The algorithm and computational results are given for the case of linear penalty functions. The modifications needed to handle the case of nonlinear penalty functions are also presented.
AB  - An efficient branch-bound algorithm is presented for solving the n-job, sequence-independent, single machine scheduling problem where the goal is to minimize the total penalty costs resulting from tardiness of jobs. The algorithm and computational results are given for the case of linear penalty functions. The modifications needed to handle the case of nonlinear penalty functions are also presented.
